‚úÖ - Yes, we can make an inner class static, which is called a static nested class in Java.
- We can't make the outer class static

class Outer {
    static int staticVar = 100;
    int instanceVar = 200;

    static class StaticInner { // ‚úÖ Static nested class
        void display() {
            System.out.println("Static variable: " + staticVar); // ‚úÖ Allowed
            // System.out.println("Instance variable: " + instanceVar); // ‚ùå Not allowed (Needs Outer class instance)
        }
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // No need to create Outer class object
        Outer.StaticInner innerObj = new Outer.StaticInner();
        innerObj.display();
    }
}

