‚úÖ A circular dependency occurs when two or more components/classes depend on each other directly or indirectly, creating a loop.
This can cause issues with dependency injection, application startup, or the design structure.

@Component
public class A {
    @Autowired
    private B b;
}

@Component
public class B {
    @Autowired
    private A a;
}

->  Decouple the business logic using a mediator/service/facade, so the two beans don‚Äôt directly depend on each other.
@Component
public class A {
    @Autowired
    private MediatorService mediator;
}

@Component
public class B {
    @Autowired
    private MediatorService mediator;
}

@Component
public class MediatorService {
    public void handleAStuff() {}
    public void handleBStuff() {}
}

